<BYLINE>By ELAINE KURTENBACH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Foreigners fleeing <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> left lovers and friends behind and came home with dark experiences instead of fond memories. Evacuees arrived in <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> on Thursday with tales of children shot down by soldiers and of acquaintances slain in the army assault on pro-democracy demonstrators in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Joanne </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>, 20, of <ORGANIZATION> Leeds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>, said students strapped the bullet-riddled body of a 9-year-old boy to a truck and paraded it through <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> to illustrate the horror. `` From the moment I saw that, I realized just how inhuman the army had been and what they had done,'' she said. `` I will never forget the sight of that little boy as long as I live.'' In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION> and airline personnel arranged for medical care, connecting flights and hotel rooms for hundreds arriving on evacuation flights chartered by the <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>. The tearful Chinese wife of a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> diplomat, who did not give her name, said: `` It was dreadful. ` We were talking with the student leaders in the square, and two days later they were dead.'' `` I had to leave my Chinese fiance behind, I hope she'll be all right,'' said <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Pritikin </PERSON>, 20, a Chinese-language student from <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. He said they parted at the <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> train station Saturday night, then the violence began and he was caught up in the rush to leave <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. Worried friends and family tried desperately to get through to <LOCATION>