e </LOCATION> -RRB- injured, with blood pouring down,'' she said. `` We saw smoke and heard gunfire. There were volleys of machine gun fire all the time and helicopters were constantly in and out of the square. `` We heard stories of old women being killed, men, women and children and of students, begging not to be shot, who were simply mowed down.'' Mrs. <PERSON> Ashbey </PERSON> and her husband, <PERSON> Roy </PERSON>, arrived in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> via <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Ashbey </PERSON> said: `` I am sickened and angry by what has happened. We had grown to really like the <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> people, who were happy and friendly. The atmosphere before the carnage was wonderful. Now I am terribly worried for the people there. I just ca n't understand how the soldiers could do what they did.'' <PERSON> Serena </PERSON> <PERSON> Carden </PERSON>, 20, of <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sussex </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>, said an <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> friend was near <LOCATION> Tiananmen </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Square </LOCATION>, `` walking along with his back to the square and they just opened fire. Someone beside him was hit and fell down at his side. He just ran.'' <PERSON> Lucy </PERSON> <PERSON> Rapaport </PERSON>, a British tour operator, said in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> the danger in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> was brought home by a <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> government announcement that the safety of foreigners could not be guaranteed. She described the situation in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION>'s antiquated airport, already disorganized by renovations, as `` chaotic, with people sleeping on the floor and lining up at check-in counters.'' <PERSON> Donna </PERSON> <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>, an <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> journalist, said: `` Anyone going into <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> now must be crazy. No one's sure who's in charge. It's dangerous. She left the Chinese capital Wednesday and was flying from <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> on Thursday.
