<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An aide's suggestion to <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION> Sen. <PERSON> Rudy </PERSON> <PERSON> Boschwitz </PERSON> has prompted a proposal for a pilot program that could lead <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> to recycle the 20,000 tons of garbage and trash generated by Capitol buildings every year. <PERSON> Boschwitz </PERSON> asked the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rules </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> to consider a recycling program for the entire Capitol complex, which includes the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Library </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and six congressional office buildings. As a result of the request from <PERSON> Boschwitz </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> members, the office of the architect of the Capitol recently proposed to begin recycling garbage from two congressional office buildings as a pilot project. `` If we do n't set the example certainly it wo n't be set elsewhere,'' <PERSON> Boschwitz </PERSON> said Thursday during a news conference by the newly formed <ORGANIZATION> Greenhouse </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Crisis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>. The foundation is dedicated to halt a global warming trend known as the `` greenhouse effect.'' One of the group's goals is to slow the cutting of forests. The Republican senator, who made a fortune in the plywood business, became interested in recycling congressional garbage at the suggestion of <PERSON> Linda </PERSON> <PERSON> Garczynski </PERSON>, a temporary staff member on loan to his office from the <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Protection </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, that it might save money, said <PERSON> Boschwitz </PERSON>' press secretary, <PERSON> Tim </PERSON> <PERSON> Droogsma </PERSON>. The Capitol Archi