<FIRST>r f PM-Goodyear-SouthAfrica     06-08 0272</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Goodyear-South Africa,0282</SECOND>
<HEAD>Goodyear Withdraws From South Africa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Rubber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> is withdrawing from <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> with the sale of a tire and general products subsidiary, citing <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> sanctions and a devalued South African currency. The sale of <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION>'s Uitenhage, <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, operations to <ORGANIZATION> Consol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> an industrial subsidiary of the South African financial, industrial and mining group <ORGANIZATION> Anglovall </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, was announced Wednesday and is subject to government approvals. Consol said the purchase price was about $ 65 million. <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> said the sale would result in a one-time charge of about $ 44 million after taxes, or 77 cents per share, to be recorded in the second quarter results, and after-tax proceeds from the sale are expected to total about $ 45 million. <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> said most of the charge would result from the recognition of a decreased value of its assets in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> related to the devaluation of the South African currency in recent years amid racial turmoil. `` While we will regret leaving <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> after providing jobs and livelihood there for 42 years, it is becoming increasingly difficult for American companies to obtain adequate returns on investments there,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Barrett </PERSON>. He added that the withdrawal also was prompted by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> sanctions, including a double <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> tax on South African earnings. <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> has described <PERSON> Anglovall </PERSON> as `` a responsible group that has demonstrated concern for human rights in the work place and has expressed intent to retain the current work force of 2,400 people,'' most of whom are non-white. <PERSON> Basil </PERSON> <PERSON> Hersov </PERSON>, chairman of Anglovall, has been on the <LOCATION> Goodyear-South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> board for 23 years.
</TEXT>
