<FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks     06-08 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-British Stocks,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices were sharply higher at midday Thursday as several favorable factors provoked some healthy buying by British institutions. Prompted by a steady pound and a rise on Wall Street, institutions entered the market in force after remaining largely on the sidelines in previous sessions, dealers said. Share prices advanced across a broad front, with special situations and takeover speculation provoking strong rises in selected blue chip issues. At midday, the <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times-Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> 100-share index was up 36.1 points, or 1.7 percent, at 2,154.0, the day's best level. Volume was a healthy 296.4 million shares, compared with 261.3 million shares at the same time Wednesday.
</TEXT>
