<SECOND>PM-Stock-Taxes,0260</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rostenkowski Asking Congress to Kill Tax Break</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: also on general news wires.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Rep. <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Rostenkowski </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ways </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Means </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, is asking <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> to kill a tax break for <ORGANIZATION> Employee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ownership </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Plans </ORGANIZATION> on grounds it has been abused by lenders. <PERSON> Rostenkowski </PERSON>, D-Ill., introduced a bill Wednesday to repeal a 1984 provision that allows banks and other lenders to escape taxes on half the income from loans made to such plans, known as ESOPs `` Once again, we have witnessed a special tax benefit provision become an abusive loophole through the ingenuity of Wall Street investment bankers,'' <PERSON> Rostenkowski </PERSON> said Wednesday. `` <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> did not intend for this special tax provision to be used in such an excessive manner.'' ESOPs were given preferential treatment under federal tax law to make it easier for employees to buy stock in the companies for which they work. In many cases, ESOPs have been used to keep alive employers threatened by bankruptcy. The government estimates that 10 million workers are covered by about 10,000 ESOPs. <PERSON> Rostenkowski </PERSON> said there is evidence that many companies are borrowing to set up ESOPs only to obtain a tax benefit while providing nothing new for employees. He noted a week-old <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> ruling that authorized public sale of bonds issued by ESOPs. That ruling, <PERSON> Rostenkowski </PERSON> said, will produce even more <ORGANIZATION> ESOP </ORGANIZATION> borrowing. He estimated the tax preference for ESOPs will cost the treasury $ 8 billion in lost revenues over five years.
</TEXT>
