<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 10am,0316</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market headed higher today, extending its recent rally fueled by takeover news and rumors and declining interest rates. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 3.49 to 2,515.81 in the first half hour of trading. Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 4 to 3 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 534 up, 389 down and 533 unchanged. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 30.41 million shares as of 10 a.m. on Wall Street. New takeover bids this week for <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> LIN </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> touched off buying in a wide range of stocks thought to be possible future candidates for acquisitions or buyouts. <ORGANIZATION> Eastman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION>, said to be a potential target, led the active list and rose -LCB- to 51. Time stock, meanwhile, dipped 2 to 168 and LIN slipped 1 -RCB- to 127 -RCB- after both experienced dramatic runups in Wednesday's trading. Beyond the takeover hubbub, analysts say the market has benefited from signs this week that the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> might be starting a change of course in its credit policy. After more than a year of tightening credit conditions, the <ORGANIZATION> Fed </ORGANIZATION> is widely believed to have made an initial step toward easing, by permitting a decline in the interest rate on federal funds, or overnight loans between banks. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks edged up .11 to 182.45. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was up .23 at 364.64. On Wednesday the <ORGANIZATION> Dow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jones </ORGANIZATION> industrial average climbed 16.00 to 2,512.32. Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 9 to 5 on the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>, with 976 up, 536 down and 493 unchanged. <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> volume totaled 213.71 million shares, against 187.57 million in the previous session.
