RGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> withdrew its rival $ 415 million buyout proposal because of failure to arrange financing. The Eastern shuttle lost many passengers to <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s rival service because of the strike and now has less than a 25 percent market share. Full-page ads for the Trump Shuttle in <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION>, the <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> Post and other East Coast papers Wednesday blared the message in giant letters: `` Starting Tomorrow, Business Travel Will Be Back on Schedule.'' The ads, as well as a similar radio version, announced that the Trump Shuttle will begin service at precisely 7 a.m. EDT today. `` Which means that now, you can go back to the time you prefer traveling _ on the hour,'' the newspaper ads read. `` What's more, when we say on the hour, we mean on the hour. Seven a.m. does not mean 7:01 a.m.'' Like Eastern did, <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> promises to roll out another plane if the first one for a given hour is full. <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION>'s shuttle offers flights leaving on the half-hour. Not to be outdone, <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> launched the `` Corporate Jet Game,'' a sweepstakes for passengers. The grand prize is free use of a 727 to fly the winner and 25 guests to a weekend trip in <LOCATION> Bermuda </LOCATION>. `` We think that we can out-Trump Mr. <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Kriendler </PERSON>. `` The battle will be won on service considerations.''
